Ahead of the 2019 general elections, the Independent National Electoral Commission, INEC has warned  political
parties against conducting fraudulent primaries. INEC also cautioned political parties against the submission of parallel lists of candidates for the various elective positions. Mahmood Yakubu, INEC Chairman gave this warning in his opening remarks at a consultative meeting with political parties in Abuja, stressing that, that a free and credible election begins with a transparent internal party primaries. Yakubu emphasized that the Commission, “has no reason to reject the name of any candidate submited by the National Working committee (NWC) of any political party through their National Chairman”. He announced that 48 political parties have fielded candidates for the forth coming governorship elections in Osun state scheduled to hold on the 22nd of September 2018. The INEC Chairman re-assured the people of Osun state of a hitch free exercise saying the election will serve as a laboratory test for the 2019 general elections. Yakubu also warned political parties and politicians against vote buying in the forthcoming Osun governorship elections and subsequently general elections. He stated that INEC together with security agencies will make arrests and prosecute those found wanting stressing that the menace cannot be carried to the next year’s polls. 